1
00:00:02,903 --> 00:00:06,038
    I CAN'T SEE ANYTHING.       
     I NEED TO GO LOWER.        


2
00:00:06,106 --> 00:00:08,973
            THE CHILD IS JUST   
            BELOW YOU, JAROD.   


3
00:00:09,043 --> 00:00:11,243
        <i> COLLAPSE IS IMMINENT.</i>  
        <i> YOU HAVE TO ABORT.</i>     


4
00:00:11,312 --> 00:00:13,645
    I CAN SAVE HIM, SYDNEY.     
     I CAN SAVE HIM!            


5
00:00:13,714 --> 00:00:16,815
    - YOU HAVE TO ABORT.        
    - NO!                       


6
00:00:16,884 --> 00:00:20,585
    <i> [ Young Jarod Yelling ]</i>    
    <i> NO!</i>                        


7
00:00:29,896 --> 00:00:32,431
                YOU'RE DEAD.    


8
00:00:33,767 --> 00:00:36,134
    I COULDA DONE IT.           
                <i> WHAT? SAVE HIM?</i>


9
00:00:36,203 --> 00:00:38,737
                YOU CAN'T SAVE  
                EVERYONE, JAROD,


10
00:00:38,805 --> 00:00:42,007
            <i> NO MATTER HOW HARD</i> 
            <i> YOU TRY.</i>           


11
00:01:36,530 --> 00:01:38,464
            [ Squeaking ]       


12
00:01:52,112 --> 00:01:54,746
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>JAROD HALSTROM.</i>                 
<i>[ Chuckles ]</i>                    


13
00:01:54,815 --> 00:01:57,982
    HE WAS THE COOLEST Ph.D.    
    WE'VE HAD IN THIS PLACE.    


14
00:01:58,051 --> 00:02:02,086
        HE HAD A PRIVATE GRANT, 
        RENTED THE LAB          
        FROM THE UNIVERSITY...  


15
00:02:02,156 --> 00:02:04,456
    AND PAID ME<i> MUCHO DINERO.</i>   


16
00:02:04,525 --> 00:02:07,492
    WHAT KIND OF RESEARCH       
    WERE YOU DOING?             
                        NADA.   


17
00:02:07,561 --> 00:02:11,963
    ALL WE DID WAS EAT PEZ,     
    WATCH FRANKENSTEIN MOVIES   
    AND PLAY WITH MICE.         


18
00:02:12,032 --> 00:02:15,100
        <i> THE LIVE ONES ANYWAY.</i>  
        LIVE ONES?              


19
00:02:15,169 --> 00:02:18,203
        YEAH, HALF OF THEM      
        WERE DEAD OR COMATOSE.  


20
00:02:18,272 --> 00:02:20,838
    SEE, JAROD USED TO          
    INJECT THEM WITH SOMETHING, 


21
00:02:20,907 --> 00:02:23,242
<i>AND THEN STARE AT THEM</i>          
<i>FOR HOURS.</i>                      


22
00:02:23,310 --> 00:02:25,210
    IT WAS KINDA GHOULISH.      


23
00:02:25,279 --> 00:02:27,912
    <i> THEN HE DONATED</i>            
    <i> HIS LITTLE CRITTERS</i>        
    <i> TO THE SCHOOL WHEN HE LEFT.</i>


24
00:02:27,981 --> 00:02:31,884
    <i> EXCEPT FOR THIS WHITE ONE.</i> 
    <i> JAROD CALLED HIM JACOB.</i>    


25
00:02:33,053 --> 00:02:35,220
        JACOB?                  


26
00:02:35,289 --> 00:02:38,290
            - HMM?              
            - NOTHING.          


27
00:02:38,359 --> 00:02:42,494
WELL, JAROD USED TO CARRY       
JACOB AROUND IN HIS POCKET      
LIKE IT WAS HIS BEST FRIEND.    


28
00:02:42,563 --> 00:02:46,465
        THEY'RE DISTANT COUSINS 
        ACTUALLY.               
<i>[ Phone Ringing ]</i>               


29
00:02:46,534 --> 00:02:48,634
            <i> EXCUSE ME.</i>         
            <i> I HAVE TO GET THAT.</i>


30
00:02:48,702 --> 00:02:53,371
    <i> NO DEAD FIREMAN</i>            
    <i> OR WOUNDED CAMERAMAN.</i>      
    <i> MAYBE HE'S GETTING BORED.</i>  


31
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:57,643
MM-MMM.                         
JAROD WILL NEVER BE BORED       
IN THE OUTSIDE WORLD.           


32
00:02:57,711 --> 00:02:59,545
HE'S TRYING TO SAVE LIVES.      


33
00:02:59,613 --> 00:03:03,648
        <i> [ Siren Wailing ]</i>      


34
00:03:03,716 --> 00:03:06,351
        WE HAVE A FEMALE,       
        LATE 20s, LEG FRACTURE, 


35
00:03:06,420 --> 00:03:08,920
<i>POSSIBLE VERTEBRAL FRACTURE</i>     
<i>WITH INTERNAL BLEEDING.</i>         


36
00:03:08,988 --> 00:03:12,891
    WE STARTED HER ON AN I.V.   
    OF NORMAL SALINE, WIDE OPEN.


37
00:03:12,960 --> 00:03:15,493
        SHE'S CODING! MOVE!     


38
00:03:16,496 --> 00:03:18,730
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.      


39
00:03:18,799 --> 00:03:22,567
    STAY WITH ME!               
     STAY WITH ME!              


40
00:03:23,770 --> 00:03:27,272
<i>[ Man Narrating ]</i>               


41
00:04:11,618 --> 00:04:13,551
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>         


42
00:04:13,620 --> 00:04:16,220
<i>[ Broots ]</i>                      
<i>UH, MISS PARKER,</i>                
<i>HAVE YOU SEEN SYDNEY?</i>           


43
00:04:16,289 --> 00:04:19,690
    - DO I LOOK LIKE A LEASH?   
    -<i> HE'S, UH, HE'S MISSING.</i>   


44
00:04:19,759 --> 00:04:21,960
            SYDNEY'S MISSING    
            WHEN HE'S HERE.     


45
00:04:22,028 --> 00:04:26,131
    WELL, ACTUALLY, HE WAS      
    A NO-SHOW AT THE SIM LAB.   


46
00:04:26,199 --> 00:04:30,802
HE LEFT FOUR SETS OF TWINS      
TWIDDLING THEIR, UH, 16 THUMBS. 


47
00:04:30,871 --> 00:04:34,472
SYDNEY'S A NO-SHOW FOR A ROOMFUL
OF HUMAN BOOKENDS?              


48
00:04:36,143 --> 00:04:39,511
[ Quietly ] SECURITY            
REPORTED SOME DRUGS MISSING...  


49
00:04:39,579 --> 00:04:41,546
        FROM THE CENTRE         
        PHARMACEUTICAL LAB.     


50
00:04:41,614 --> 00:04:44,516
        A NURSE SAYS SHE        
        SAW SYDNEY LEAVING THERE
        EARLY THIS MORNING.     


51
00:04:44,584 --> 00:04:46,818
        <i> [ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>
I'LL TALK TO YOU LATER.         


52
00:04:46,887 --> 00:04:50,488
<i>[ Elevator Bell Dings ]</i>         


53
00:04:50,557 --> 00:04:53,358
    - [ Chattering ]            
    - YOUR DAUGHTER NEEDS YOU.  


54
00:04:53,427 --> 00:04:55,193
    [ Chattering Continues ]    


55
00:04:55,262 --> 00:04:57,929
    - TRAUMA FIVE, STAT.        
    - SHE HAS A LITTLE GIRL.    


56
00:04:57,997 --> 00:05:00,331
OKAY, WE'LL TAKE IT             
FROM HERE, JAROD. JAROD.        


57
00:05:00,401 --> 00:05:02,767
    SHE HAS A LITTLE GIRL.      
SOMEONE GET HIM                 
OFF MY PATIENT.                 


58
00:05:02,836 --> 00:05:04,335
            JAROD, WE'RE DONE.  


59
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,240
<i>[ Water Running ]</i>               


60
00:05:11,278 --> 00:05:15,046
            ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.
            I'M GONNA STAY HERE 
            FOR A WHILE.        


61
00:05:15,115 --> 00:05:17,115
    SHE'S GOIN' INTO SURGERY.   
I KNOW.                         


62
00:05:17,183 --> 00:05:19,250
I JUST WANNA MAKE SURE          
SHE'S ALL RIGHT.                


63
00:05:19,319 --> 00:05:21,686
                OH, NO, NO, NO. 
                LOOK.           


64
00:05:21,755 --> 00:05:25,189
        OKAY, I'VE BEEN ONLY    
        DRIVING WITH YOU, WHAT, 
        A COUPLE WEEKS, RIGHT?  


65
00:05:25,258 --> 00:05:28,460
    TAKE MY WORD FOR IT. YOU GET
    TOO PERSONAL WITH A CLIENT, 


66
00:05:28,528 --> 00:05:31,395
    THAT'S JUST ENERGY YOU CAN'T
    SPEND SAVING THE NEXT ONE.  


67
00:05:31,464 --> 00:05:35,433
    ALL RIGHT? WE DO OUR BEST   
    FOR THESE PEOPLE,           
    THEN WE MOVE ON.            


68
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:38,303
        YOU CAN'T TRAIN YOURSELF
        TO THINK THAT WAY,      
        THIS JOB WILL KILL YOU. 


69
00:05:38,372 --> 00:05:40,471
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>NOT IF I DO IT FIRST.</i>           


70
00:05:40,540 --> 00:05:45,610
WHY DON'T I HAVE PROPER         
TREATMENT REPORTS               
ON YOUR LAST FIVE DELIVERIES?   


71
00:05:45,679 --> 00:05:48,312
                    DELIVERIES? 
        <i> DR. FLETCHER,</i>          
        <i> MEET JAROD RANDOLPH.</i>   


72
00:05:48,381 --> 00:05:52,150
I HOPE YOUR PARTNER'S           
BETTER AT DRIVING THEM IN THAN  
HE IS AT DOING HIS PAPERWORK.   


73
00:05:53,787 --> 00:05:57,422
I WILL GET TO THAT PAPERWORK    
WHEN I GET A BREAK, ALL RIGHT?  
I PROMISE.                      


74
00:05:57,491 --> 00:05:59,457
YOU BETTER.                     


75
00:06:02,663 --> 00:06:04,896
        [ Beeping ]             


76
00:06:06,933 --> 00:06:10,769
<i>[ Miss Parker ]</i>                 
<i>SYDNEY MADE QUITE A HEIST</i>       
<i>FROM THE CENTRE PHARMACY.</i>       


77
00:06:10,837 --> 00:06:14,405
<i>CYLIN,</i>                          
<i>TRIPHENYLMIDE,</i>                  


78
00:06:14,474 --> 00:06:16,407
        D-- UH--                


79
00:06:16,476 --> 00:06:19,610
DIFLUTAZENIL.                   
UH, A REVERSAL AGENT,           


80
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:23,148
A NEUROSTIMULANT                
AND AN ANTIDEPRESSANT.          


81
00:06:23,216 --> 00:06:25,083
    HUH.                        


82
00:06:25,152 --> 00:06:26,851
                GREAT. GREAT.   


83
00:06:26,920 --> 00:06:29,587
    NOW SYDNEY WILL TURN UP     
    IN SOME HOP HOUSE, AND WE'LL
    LOSE JAROD'S TRAIL AGAIN.   


84
00:06:29,656 --> 00:06:33,724
    START DECRYPTING HIS FILES. 
    MAYBE THERE'S A CLUE THERE. 


85
00:06:35,462 --> 00:06:39,497
        UH-- UM--               
        [ Clears Throat ]       
                <i> [ Keyboarding ]</i>


86
00:06:39,566 --> 00:06:42,867
YOU'RE--                        
YOU'RE INVADING MY SPACE.       


87
00:06:50,677 --> 00:06:53,545
CLOSE IS GOOD.                  


88
00:06:53,613 --> 00:06:55,713
<i>[ Chattering ]</i>                  


89
00:06:59,920 --> 00:07:03,288
WHY IS THERE A SEVERED          
ANIMAL'S LIMB HANGING           
FROM YOUR REARVIEW MIRROR?      


90
00:07:03,356 --> 00:07:06,824
        IT'S A RABBIT'S FOOT.   
TECHNICALLY, IT'S A PAW.        


91
00:07:06,893 --> 00:07:09,127
            WHAT, YOU MEAN      
            YOU'VE NEVER SEEN   
            ONE OF THOSE BEFORE?


92
00:07:09,196 --> 00:07:11,729
                    IT'S LUCKY. 
NOT FOR                         
THE THREE-LEGGED RABBIT.        


93
00:07:11,798 --> 00:07:13,731
<i>[ Dispatcher, Indistinct ]</i>      


94
00:07:13,801 --> 00:07:15,667
                SURE, YEAH.     
                COFFEE TIME.    


95
00:07:15,735 --> 00:07:18,969
<i>WOULD YOU GUYS KEEP IT DOWN?</i>    
<i>I'M TRYING TO SLEEP HERE.</i>       


96
00:07:20,274 --> 00:07:23,775
    YOU MIGHT GET MORE REST     
    IF YOU TURN DOWN YOUR MUSIC.


97
00:07:23,844 --> 00:07:27,011
    SELF-HYPNOSIS.              
    TRYING TO STUDY             
    WHILE I SLEEP.              


98
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:30,348
        <i> THE NEW ENGLAND</i>        
        <i> JOURNAL OF MEDICINE.</i>   
         I'M IMPRESSED.         


99
00:07:30,417 --> 00:07:33,050
YEAH? TELL THE ADMISSIONS BOARD 
AT ATLANTA.                     


100
00:07:33,119 --> 00:07:37,054
<i>I AM OUT OF THE E.M.T. BUSINESS</i> 
<i>COME THIS FALL,</i>                 
<i>WITH A LITTLE LUCK.</i>             


101
00:07:37,123 --> 00:07:39,857
            HAVE YOU TRIED      
            A RABBIT'S FOOT?    


102
00:07:39,927 --> 00:07:43,461
I'M A FOUR-LEAF CLOVER          
PERSON MYSELF.                  
<i>OH, MAN, VARGAS IS HERE.</i>        


103
00:07:43,530 --> 00:07:47,432
                WHO'S VARGAS?   
    MAX VARGAS,                 
    STATE BOARD OF INSPECTION.  


104
00:07:47,500 --> 00:07:50,368
I DIDN'T THINK THE INSPECTION   
WAS GOING TO BE                 
FOR ANOTHER TWO WEEKS.          


105
00:07:50,437 --> 00:07:53,604
THIS GUY IS                     
A BIGGER PAIN IN THE ASS        
THAN THE SUITS AT THE HOSPITAL. 


106
00:07:53,673 --> 00:07:57,942
<i>ARE THOSE THE SAME PAINS</i>        
<i>IN THE ASS WHO CALL ME AT HOME</i>  
<i>LOOKING FOR THEIR PAPERWORK?</i>    


107
00:07:58,011 --> 00:08:02,246
YOU MUST BE RANDOLPH.           
WHAT'S IT LIKE BEING            
INDEPENDENTLY WEALTHY?          


108
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:05,049
            I BEG YOUR PARDON?  
WELL, YOU'VE BEEN               
HERE A MONTH...                 


109
00:08:05,118 --> 00:08:08,620
AND YOU HAVEN'T DONE YOUR W-4,  
SO YOU MUST HAVE A LITTLE       
NEST EGG STASHED AWAY SOMEWHERE.


110
00:08:08,689 --> 00:08:10,621
            IT MUST HAVE SLIPPED
            THROUGH THE CRACKS. 


111
00:08:10,690 --> 00:08:12,924
WELL, IT'S MY JOB               
TO FILL IN THOSE CRACKS.        


112
00:08:12,993 --> 00:08:15,927
MAYBE YOU AND I                 
SHOULD GO TO THE OFFICE         
AND FILL THESE FORMS IN,        


113
00:08:15,996 --> 00:08:18,196
SO THE BOOKS                    
HAVE A SEMBLANCE OF ORDER.      


114
00:08:18,264 --> 00:08:22,533
<i>OH, UH, MR. VARGAS, JAROD AND I</i> 
<i>HAVE A UNION-GUARANTEED</i>         
<i>COFFEE BREAK NOW.</i>               


115
00:08:22,602 --> 00:08:24,769
YOU'LL BE USING IT              
TO FILL OUT THESE FORMS.        


116
00:08:24,838 --> 00:08:27,539
    I'LL HAVE THEM ON YOUR DESK 
    FIRST THING IN THE MORNING. 


117
00:08:27,608 --> 00:08:29,573
    SEE THAT YOU DO.            


118
00:08:32,545 --> 00:08:35,613
<i>[ Rolling Thunder ]</i>             


119
00:08:40,287 --> 00:08:42,820
IT'S SWEET THAT YOU             
TALK TO HIM, SYDNEY.            


120
00:08:42,889 --> 00:08:45,423
SOME PEOPLE THINK               
THEY'RE NOT AWARE.              
                        HMM.    


121
00:08:45,492 --> 00:08:48,659
HE NEEDS TO KNOW                
HE'S NOT ALONE.                 


122
00:08:48,728 --> 00:08:51,629
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>             
<i>JACOB.</i>                          


123
00:08:51,698 --> 00:08:56,901
I HAVE DISCOVERED               
THIS EXPERIMENTAL RESEARCH--    


124
00:08:56,969 --> 00:08:58,937
THE HALSTROM TECHNIQUE.         


125
00:08:59,006 --> 00:09:01,006
<i>JAROD SENT IT TO ME.</i>            


126
00:09:01,074 --> 00:09:04,308
<i>IT'S A LONG SHOT,</i>               
<i>BUT IT'S OUR BEST HOPE.</i>         


127
00:09:04,377 --> 00:09:08,079
I PROMISED YOU...               


128
00:09:08,147 --> 00:09:10,248
I WOULD NEVER GIVE UP.          


129
00:09:10,316 --> 00:09:13,918
<i>-[ Honking, Crashing ]</i>          
<i>-[ Young Jacob ] SYDNEY! SYDNEY!</i>


130
00:09:23,797 --> 00:09:26,164
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>             


131
00:10:02,769 --> 00:10:05,069
<i>[ Mr. Chambers Reading ]</i>        
<i>"WHILE SYDNEY CARTON...</i>         


132
00:10:05,138 --> 00:10:07,938
<i>"AND THE SHEEP OF THE PRISONS</i>   
<i> WERE IN THE ADJOINING</i>          
<i> DARK ROOM,</i>                     


133
00:10:08,007 --> 00:10:10,441
<i>"SPEAKING SO LOW</i>                
<i> THAT NOT A SOUND WAS HEARD,</i>    


134
00:10:10,510 --> 00:10:14,846
    MR. LORRY LOOKED AT JERRY   
    IN CONSIDERABLE DOUBT       
    AND MISTRUST."              


135
00:10:27,060 --> 00:10:31,228
[ Jarod ] HE'S A STOCKBROKER    
FROM ALPHARETTA.                
HIS NAME IS JERRY MITCHELL.     


136
00:10:31,297 --> 00:10:35,566
QUEEN OF MERCY, THIS IS UNIT 45.
WE'VE GOT A MALE, MID 50s,      
POSSIBLE HEAD TRAUMA, YOU COPY? 


137
00:10:35,635 --> 00:10:38,369
QUEEN OF MERCY?                 
COUNTY GENERAL'S CLOSER.        


138
00:10:38,438 --> 00:10:41,372
            QUEEN OF MERCY'S GOT
            THE BEST HEAD TRAUMA
            CENTER IN ATLANTA.  


139
00:10:41,441 --> 00:10:43,675
I UNDERSTAND THAT,              
BUT THIS GENTLEMAN              
NEEDS IMMEDIATE--               


140
00:10:43,744 --> 00:10:46,210
            STABILIZE HIM.      
            I'LL DO THE DRIVING.


141
00:10:49,182 --> 00:10:51,515
    WE COULD HAVE HAD HIM       
    IN TREATMENT AT COUNTY      
    EIGHT MINUTES AGO.          


142
00:10:51,584 --> 00:10:54,152
    HEY, OUR STOCKBROKER        
    COULDN'T BE IN BETTER HANDS.


143
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:56,554
    THAT'S WORTH EIGHT MINUTES  
    OF HIS TIME.                
    I HOPE YOU'RE RIGHT.        


144
00:10:59,426 --> 00:11:01,592
    I MADE A JUDGMENT CALL.     
    YOU GOT A PROBLEM WITH THAT?


145
00:11:02,963 --> 00:11:04,896
NO. NO PROBLEM.                 


146
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:11,803
    [ Clears Throat ]           
    NOTHING OBVIOUS             
    ON SYDNEY'S E-MAIL.         


147
00:11:11,872 --> 00:11:14,672
PHONE RECORDS                   
ARE ALL CENTRE RELATED.         


148
00:11:16,409 --> 00:11:19,777
YOU'D THINK HE'D OCCASIONALLY   
CALL A 900 NUMBER               
TO SPICE UP HIS LIFE.           


149
00:11:19,846 --> 00:11:22,146
    WHAT ABOUT                  
    HIS REGULAR MAIL?           


150
00:11:22,215 --> 00:11:25,783
         MEDICAL JOURNALS,      
        <i> PLANT WORLD</i> MAGAZINE.  


151
00:11:25,852 --> 00:11:27,719
        <i> BOOK OF THE WEEK CLUB.</i> 
GIVE ME THAT.                   


152
00:11:37,130 --> 00:11:39,330
ANNUAL DONATION                 
TO THE MOUNT PLEASANT HOME.     


153
00:11:39,399 --> 00:11:42,066
    AN HISTORICAL SOCIETY MAYBE?


154
00:11:42,135 --> 00:11:44,402
IT'S WHERE HE GOES              
FOR CHRISTMAS EVERY YEAR.       


155
00:11:44,471 --> 00:11:49,073
        DR. COREY.              
        I OWE YOU AN APOLOGY.   


156
00:11:49,142 --> 00:11:52,844
<i>I SHOULD HAVE RELINQUISHED</i>      
<i>THE GURNEY. ONCE WE'RE</i>          
<i>IN THE E.R., IT'S YOUR PATIENT.</i> 


157
00:11:52,913 --> 00:11:56,447
DON'T SWEAT IT, JAROD.          
AT LEAST YOUR HEART             
WAS IN THE RIGHT PLACE.         


158
00:11:56,515 --> 00:12:00,751
<i>BY THE WAY,</i>                     
<i>THAT YOUNG MOTHER YOU BROUGHT IN</i>
<i>IS GOING TO BE FINE.</i>            


159
00:12:00,820 --> 00:12:03,187
            THAT'S WONDERFUL.   


160
00:12:03,256 --> 00:12:05,889
I'M NOT USED TO                 
SEEING AN E.M.S.'er             
GET SO PERSONALLY INVOLVED.     


161
00:12:05,958 --> 00:12:07,892
    I FIND IT DIFFICULT NOT TO. 


162
00:12:07,961 --> 00:12:10,094
        SOMETIMES I FEEL LIKE   
        I KNOW WHAT MY PATIENT  
        IS GOING THROUGH.       


163
00:12:10,163 --> 00:12:12,497
I KNOW WHAT YOU MEAN.           


164
00:12:12,565 --> 00:12:14,999
    IS THAT WHY YOU'RE          
    FOLLOWING UP WITH STEVEN?   


165
00:12:16,703 --> 00:12:18,636
<i>I'VE SEEN THIS INJURY</i>           
<i>A HUNDRED TIMES,</i>                


166
00:12:18,705 --> 00:12:23,374
<i>AND I'M USUALLY ABLE</i>            
<i>TO STABILIZE THE PATIENT,</i>       
<i>BUT THIS ONE--</i>                  


167
00:12:23,443 --> 00:12:25,843
<i>IT'S LIKE I PULLED OUT</i>          
<i>ALL THE STOPS,</i>                  


168
00:12:25,912 --> 00:12:28,212
BUT HE STILL                    
GOT AWAY FROM ME.               


169
00:12:28,281 --> 00:12:31,849
            <i> STEVEN IS LUCKY</i>    
            <i> TO HAVE A DOCTOR</i>   
            <i> THAT CARES SO MUCH.</i>


170
00:12:36,656 --> 00:12:39,457
            ARE YOU OKAY?       


171
00:12:39,526 --> 00:12:43,528
IT'S JUST THAT YOU CAN'T        
ALWAYS HELP THEM ENOUGH,        
AND I DON'T LIKE THAT FEELING.  


172
00:12:43,597 --> 00:12:45,896
        WELL, I THINK           
        THAT GOES WITH THE JOB. 


173
00:12:45,965 --> 00:12:49,667
IT DOESN'T MAKE IT              
ANY EASIER TO LIVE WITH.        


174
00:12:49,736 --> 00:12:52,036
            YOU'RE NOT THINKING 
            OF TRANSFERRING     
            SOMEPLACE ELSE?     


175
00:12:53,973 --> 00:12:57,075
THERE'S A RESEARCH POSITION     
AT CORNELL MED.                 


176
00:12:57,144 --> 00:12:59,710
I'M THINKING                    
I'LL HAVE AN EASIER TIME        
DEALING WITH THE MICE.          


177
00:12:59,779 --> 00:13:01,679
                DON'T BE SO SURE
                ABOUT THAT.     


178
00:13:01,748 --> 00:13:04,115
            LOOK, DO YOURSELF   
            A FAVOR.            


179
00:13:04,183 --> 00:13:06,850
            REALLY THINK        
            ABOUT YOUR DECISION.


180
00:13:06,920 --> 00:13:10,254
        THIS HOSPITAL           
        NEEDS PEOPLE LIKE YOU.  


181
00:13:16,663 --> 00:13:19,764
            "IT IS A FAR,       
             FAR BETTER THING   
             THAT I DO,         


182
00:13:22,802 --> 00:13:27,004
        <i> "THAN I HAVE EVER DONE;</i>


183
00:13:27,073 --> 00:13:30,274
<i>"IT IS A FAR, FAR BETTER REST</i>   
<i> THAT I GO TO,</i>                  


184
00:13:30,343 --> 00:13:33,010
        <i> THAN I'VE EVER KNOWN."</i> 


185
00:13:33,079 --> 00:13:35,914
            HOW ABOUT A BREAK   
            BEFORE WE START     
            THE NEXT BOOK?      


186
00:13:38,985 --> 00:13:42,187
    -<i> HE LIKES DICKENS.</i>         
    - DICKENS IS HOPEFUL.       


187
00:13:43,289 --> 00:13:47,124
EVEN HIS SADDEST ENDINGS        
ARE UPLIFTING.                  


188
00:13:47,193 --> 00:13:49,560
I BROUGHT YOU SOME COCOA.       


189
00:13:51,797 --> 00:13:54,899
            <i> APPRECIATE</i>         
            <i> YOUR VISITS, JAROD.</i>


190
00:13:54,968 --> 00:13:57,936
        <i> YOU'D THINK YOU'D GET</i>  
        <i> ENOUGH OF HOSPITALS</i>    
        <i> IN YOUR LINE OF WORK.</i>  


191
00:13:58,004 --> 00:14:00,104
<i>WELL, THIS HOSPITAL</i>             
<i>COULD USE SOME MORE VOLUNTEERS.</i> 


192
00:14:00,173 --> 00:14:02,373
HOW'S STEVEN DOING?             


193
00:14:02,442 --> 00:14:05,075
    <i> THEY STARTED HIM</i>           
    <i> ON A NEW TREATMENT CALLED</i>  
    <i> THE TREFOIL THERAPY.</i>       


194
00:14:05,144 --> 00:14:10,148
IT WAS DEVELOPED AT YALE.       
IT DELIVERS NEUROSTIMULANTS     
DIRECTLY TO THE HYPOTHALAMUS.   


195
00:14:13,486 --> 00:14:15,619
UM, I HAVE A FRIEND             
WHO'S IN A COMA.                


196
00:14:17,891 --> 00:14:19,957
            THEY SAY IT HAS     
            A 20% SUCCESS RATE. 


197
00:14:20,026 --> 00:14:22,159
            <i> ONE OUT OF FIVE</i>    
            <i> COMES OUT OF IT.</i>   


198
00:14:22,228 --> 00:14:25,563
    - AND FOUR DON'T.           
    - HE FITS THE PROFILE.      


199
00:14:27,066 --> 00:14:30,468
    <i> THEY SAID IF ANYONE</i>        
    <i> WOULD ACCEPT THE TREATMENT,</i>


200
00:14:30,537 --> 00:14:32,436
                <i> STEVEN WOULD.</i>  


201
00:14:33,506 --> 00:14:35,340
            HE'S A FIGHTER.     


202
00:14:35,408 --> 00:14:37,442
                    <i> RIGHT, HON?</i>
                    RIGHT.      


203
00:14:39,845 --> 00:14:43,114
    DO YOU MIND?                


204
00:14:43,183 --> 00:14:45,116
SO, STEVEN WAS A WRESTLER.      


205
00:14:45,185 --> 00:14:48,652
            TOOK FIRST PLACE    
            IN THE STATE FINALS 
            HIS SENIOR YEAR.    


206
00:14:49,956 --> 00:14:52,156
    <i> HE WAS BEHIND IN TWO</i>       
    <i> OUT OF HIS FIVE MATCHES.</i>   


207
00:14:52,225 --> 00:14:55,292
            BUT HE CAME BACK.   
            PULLED IT OUT.      


208
00:14:55,361 --> 00:14:57,928
WELL, YOU MUST BE               
VERY PROUD.                     


209
00:14:57,997 --> 00:15:01,866
            HE NEVER GAVE UP.   
            WE'D CHEER HIM      
            FROM THE STANDS.    


210
00:15:01,934 --> 00:15:05,270
        <i> I THINK HEARING US</i>     
        <i> MADE HIM TRY HARDER.</i>   


211
00:15:09,876 --> 00:15:14,678
BUT I REALLY DO BELIEVE         
THAT PEOPLE IN A COMA--         


212
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:17,248
THEY HEAR EVERYTHING            
THAT GOES ON AROUND THEM.       


213
00:15:19,452 --> 00:15:21,386
ENJOY THE COCOA.                


214
00:15:26,059 --> 00:15:29,627
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>               
<i>DR. MICHAELS TO ADMITTING.</i>      
<i>DR. MICHAELS TO ADMITTING.</i>      


215
00:15:29,696 --> 00:15:32,897
                "CHAPTER ONE.   


216
00:15:32,965 --> 00:15:36,234
"TREATS OF THE PLACE            
 WHERE OLIVER TWIST WAS BORN... 


217
00:15:36,302 --> 00:15:39,337
<i>AND OF THE CIRCUMSTANCES</i>        
<i>ATTENDING HIS BIRTH."</i>           


218
00:15:39,405 --> 00:15:41,839
<i>WELL, ARE YOU GONNA</i>             
<i>OPEN THE LETTER?</i>                


219
00:15:41,908 --> 00:15:43,841
                    YES.        


220
00:15:45,378 --> 00:15:49,347
        WAIT, WAIT, WAIT, WAIT. 
        FOR GOOD LUCK.          


221
00:15:49,416 --> 00:15:54,051
ALL RIGHT. I'LL OPEN IT.        
[ Exhales ]                     


222
00:15:54,120 --> 00:15:56,721
OH, MY GOD.                     


223
00:15:56,790 --> 00:15:59,223
    I'M... IN!                  
                    ALL RIGHT!  


224
00:15:59,292 --> 00:16:01,325
            YOU'RE GONNA MAKE   
            A WONDERFUL DOCTOR. 


225
00:16:01,394 --> 00:16:06,163
        I'D BETTER BE.          
        I'M ABOUT TO BE         
        $100,000 IN DEBT.       


226
00:16:06,232 --> 00:16:08,499
IF IT ISN'T                     
THE INVISIBLE MAN.              


227
00:16:08,568 --> 00:16:12,236
                <i> I SHOULD, UH,</i>  
                <i> CALL MY FAMILY</i> 
                <i> WITH THE NEWS.</i> 


228
00:16:16,943 --> 00:16:19,543
I FOLLOWED THROUGH              
ON YOUR PAPERWORK.              


229
00:16:19,612 --> 00:16:22,413
NOT ONLY HAVE YOU NOT FILED     
YOUR PAYROLL DOCUMENTS,         


230
00:16:22,481 --> 00:16:26,617
YOU DON'T SEEM TO               
HAVE ANY DOCUMENTS              
THAT SUPPORT YOUR IDENTITY.     


231
00:16:26,686 --> 00:16:29,286
AS FAR AS I'M CONCERNED,        
YOU DON'T EXIST.                


232
00:16:29,355 --> 00:16:32,223
I WANT YOUR NAME,               
YOUR ADDRESS,                   


233
00:16:32,292 --> 00:16:36,227
YOUR SOCIAL SECURITY NUMBER     
YOUR NEXT OF KIN,               
YOUR REFERENCES.                


234
00:16:36,296 --> 00:16:39,597
THE WHOLE KIT,                  
THE WHOLE CABOODLE,             
I WANT IT NOW.                  


235
00:16:39,665 --> 00:16:42,266
    - RIGHT AFTER LUNCH.        
    - YOU BETTER GET WRITING,   


236
00:16:42,335 --> 00:16:45,870
            OR I'M TAKING YOU   
            OFF THE STREETS.    


237
00:16:45,939 --> 00:16:48,239
[ Monitor Beeping ]             


238
00:16:58,751 --> 00:17:02,953
    LET'S INCREASE THE, UH,     
    CYLIN TO 436 MILLIGRAM      
    PER LITER.                  


239
00:17:03,022 --> 00:17:07,958
        AND THE DIFLUTAZENIL,   
        LET'S GO 275.           
                <i> ALL RIGHT.</i>     


240
00:17:14,767 --> 00:17:16,968
    YOU'VE BEEN MISSING         
    FOR THREE DAYS, JACOB.      


241
00:17:17,037 --> 00:17:19,303
I CAN'T KEEP COVERING FOR YOU   
WITH MR. RAINES.                


242
00:17:19,372 --> 00:17:21,939
    I'VE HAD PERSONAL BUSINESS. 


243
00:17:22,008 --> 00:17:23,974
YOU NEVER KEPT SECRETS FROM ME. 


244
00:17:24,043 --> 00:17:28,479
SYDNEY, I--                     
I HAVE ETHICAL CONCERNS         
ABOUT OUR WORK.                 


245
00:17:28,547 --> 00:17:30,948
DON'T START WITH THAT RUBBISH.  
WE'RE NOT DOING ANYTHING WRONG. 


246
00:17:31,017 --> 00:17:34,285
OPEN YOUR EYES, SYDNEY.         
        <i> THEY ARE OPEN, JACOB.</i>  


247
00:17:34,354 --> 00:17:37,688
    I SEE THE OPPORTUNITY       
    TO DO WHAT WE'VE BEEN       
    WORKING FOR ALL OUR LIVES.  


248
00:17:37,757 --> 00:17:42,293
GET YOUR MIND OFF OF YOUR CAREER
FOR ONE SECOND, WILL YOU?       
I'M TALKING ABOUT THE CHILDREN. 


249
00:17:42,362 --> 00:17:46,263
        <i> [ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i> 


250
00:17:49,235 --> 00:17:52,269
        [ Jarod ]               
        HELLO, SYDNEY.          
        ANY PROGRESS?           


251
00:17:52,338 --> 00:17:55,139
        <i> [ Sydney ]</i>             
        <i> HALSTROM'S TECHNIQUE,</i>  
        <i> IT'S JUST BRILLIANT.</i>   


252
00:17:55,208 --> 00:17:57,541
     IT COULD HELP              
     A GREAT MANY PEOPLE.       


253
00:17:57,610 --> 00:18:00,477
ONE AT A TIME.                  
HOW'S JACOB?                    


254
00:18:00,546 --> 00:18:03,313
                NOTHING YET,    
                I'M AFRAID.     


255
00:18:03,382 --> 00:18:05,716
        TELL ME, JAROD.         
        WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS? 


256
00:18:05,785 --> 00:18:10,521
THE MEDICAL PROFESSION.         
IT'S ABOUT THE RELIEF           
OF SUFFERING.                   


257
00:18:10,590 --> 00:18:13,090
    REMEMBER?                   


258
00:18:13,159 --> 00:18:15,259
    [ Phone Beeps ]             


259
00:18:39,485 --> 00:18:41,719
        ♪♪ [ Whistling ]        


260
00:18:48,361 --> 00:18:51,929
HEY, JACOB. JACOB,              
HOW YOU DOING? HOW YOU DOING?   


261
00:18:51,998 --> 00:18:53,931
<i>DID YOU HAVE</i>                    
<i>A GOOD DAY? HMM?</i>                


262
00:19:03,242 --> 00:19:05,342
DR. COREY, GOOD MORNING.        
                        HEY.    


263
00:19:05,412 --> 00:19:09,013
I WANTED TO CHECK ON THE STATUS 
OF THE STOCKBROKER THAT RENNERT 
AND I BROUGHT IN YESTERDAY.     


264
00:19:09,081 --> 00:19:10,948
    WE DAMN NEAR HAD TO         
    LIFE-FLIGHT HIM TO COUNTY.  


265
00:19:11,016 --> 00:19:14,118
I THOUGHT THIS HOSPITAL         
HAD THE BEST HEAD TRAUMA UNIT   
IN THE CITY.                    


266
00:19:14,187 --> 00:19:18,022
    HEAD TRAUMA WAS DOWNGRADED  
    MONTHS AGO, ALONG WITH      
    A THIRD OF OUR BUDGET.      


267
00:19:18,091 --> 00:19:22,059
        YOU GUYS SHOULD KEEP UP 
        WITH CURRENT EVENTS.    


268
00:19:27,033 --> 00:19:29,366
                WHAT'S WITH HER?


269
00:19:29,435 --> 00:19:32,937
SHE'S LIKE YOU.                 
SHE CARES TOO MUCH.             


270
00:19:33,006 --> 00:19:35,906
                    [ Chuckles ]


271
00:19:35,975 --> 00:19:38,342
                I CAN'T WAIT    
                TILL THURSDAY.  


272
00:19:38,410 --> 00:19:41,078
    - WHAT HAPPENS ON THURSDAY? 
    - MY TRANSFER CAME THROUGH. 


273
00:19:41,147 --> 00:19:43,947
    - I AM OUT OF THE E.R.      
    - SARAH.                    


274
00:19:45,151 --> 00:19:47,718
THEY NEED YOU HERE.             


275
00:19:47,787 --> 00:19:51,289
[ Chuckles ]                    
LOOK, I HAVE BEEN THROUGH THIS  
WITH EVERYONE I KNOW.           


276
00:19:51,357 --> 00:19:53,491
        I'LL GIVE YOUR REGARDS  
        TO THE MICE.            


277
00:19:56,662 --> 00:19:58,595
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>LET'S GO! LET'S MOVE!</i>           
<i>RIGHT IN HERE!</i>                  


278
00:19:58,665 --> 00:20:00,631
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>WHAT DO YOU GOT?</i>                
        [ Chattering ]          


279
00:20:19,285 --> 00:20:21,552
<i>[ Woman On P.A. ]</i>               
<i>DR. FLETCHER</i>                    
<i>TO ADMINISTRATION, PLEASE.</i>      


280
00:20:21,621 --> 00:20:24,188
<i>DR. FLETCHER</i>                    
<i>TO ADMINISTRATION.</i>              


281
00:20:42,575 --> 00:20:44,575
SYDNEY.                         


282
00:20:46,879 --> 00:20:49,613
SO, WHO'S MR. X?                
        NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.  


283
00:20:49,682 --> 00:20:52,816
YOUR BUSINESS                   
IS MY BUSINESS.                 


284
00:20:52,885 --> 00:20:55,485
                JAROD CAN WAIT. 


285
00:20:57,256 --> 00:21:01,893
I CAN'T.                        
GO PACK YOUR BAGS.              
YOU'RE COMING WITH ME.          


286
00:21:01,961 --> 00:21:04,328
    YOU ARE NOT WELCOME HERE.   


287
00:21:09,636 --> 00:21:12,402
ALL I HAVE TO DO                
IS CALL THE SWEEPER TEAM.       


288
00:21:13,773 --> 00:21:15,706
            MM-HMM.             


289
00:21:22,782 --> 00:21:25,082
        I HAVE PRIORITIES.      


290
00:21:26,752 --> 00:21:29,453
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>             


291
00:21:56,883 --> 00:21:59,216
    WHO WAS ON DUTY LAST NIGHT? 


292
00:21:59,285 --> 00:22:02,285
WHO WAS ON DU--                 
SOMEBODY WAS HERE LAST NIGHT?   
WHO WAS ON DUTY?                


293
00:22:05,892 --> 00:22:08,192
DON'T YOU HAVE THAT             
IN ONE OF YOUR FILES?           


294
00:22:08,261 --> 00:22:10,461
    - IF I DID, WOULD I ASK YOU?
    - WHAT DID YOU LOSE?        


295
00:22:10,530 --> 00:22:15,199
    THERE'S SOME                
    PERSONNEL FILES MISSING,    
    INCLUDING YOURS, I MAY ADD. 


296
00:22:15,267 --> 00:22:18,102
WELL, I'M NOT GOING TO          
FILL OUT ANY MORE PAPERWORK.    


297
00:22:18,171 --> 00:22:21,739
            YOU WON'T HAVE TO,  
            RANDOLPH. JAROD.    


298
00:22:21,808 --> 00:22:24,175
            <i> BORN IN SEATTLE.</i>   


299
00:22:24,243 --> 00:22:26,610
        <i> ATTENDED</i>               
        <i> MILLBROOK ELEMENTARY.</i>  


300
00:22:27,680 --> 00:22:29,613
            PHOTOGRAPHIC MEMORY.


301
00:22:30,849 --> 00:22:33,784
    AND I'M SURE I HAVE         
    ENOUGH IN HERE RIGHT NOW... 


302
00:22:33,852 --> 00:22:36,754
    TO RUN A BACKGROUND CHECK   
    ON YOU.                     


303
00:22:41,493 --> 00:22:44,995
I'M THINKING ABOUT              
GOING INTO PEDIATRICS.          
WHAT DO YOU THINK?              


304
00:22:45,064 --> 00:22:48,599
    I THINK A DOCTOR            
    NEEDS TO HAVE               
    A STRONG SENSE OF ETHICS.   


305
00:22:48,667 --> 00:22:52,602
WHAT?                           
HEY, WHERE WE GOING?            


306
00:22:52,671 --> 00:22:55,906
<i>[ Jarod ] TRYING OUT</i>            
<i>A DIFFERENT ROUTE TODAY.</i>        
            <i> DIFFERENT ROUTE?</i>   


307
00:22:55,974 --> 00:22:59,643
    MM-HMM.                     
    PEACHTREE ATHLETIC CENTER   
    TO QUEEN OF MERCY HOSPITAL. 


308
00:22:59,712 --> 00:23:04,414
<i>IT'S INTERESTING.</i>               
<i>THERE ARE TWO OTHER HOSPITALS</i>   
<i>THAT ARE MUCH CLOSER BY.</i>        


309
00:23:04,483 --> 00:23:06,984
    NEITHER ONE OF THEM         
    ARE QUEEN OF MERCY.         


310
00:23:07,052 --> 00:23:11,321
- WHAT ARE YOU TALKING ABOUT?   
- ETHICS.                       


311
00:23:17,930 --> 00:23:20,865
    STEVEN CHAMBERS WAS INJURED 
    DURING A WRESTLING MATCH.   


312
00:23:20,933 --> 00:23:26,870
YOU AND RENNERT TOOK HIM ALL    
THE WAY FROM THE ATHLETIC CENTER
TO QUEEN OF MERCY HOSPITAL.     


313
00:23:26,939 --> 00:23:28,973
        EXPLAIN TO ME           
        WHY A SEASONED E.M.T....


314
00:23:29,041 --> 00:23:31,875
WOULD TAKE A CRITICAL PATIENT   
SO FAR OUT OF THE LOOP.         


315
00:23:31,944 --> 00:23:36,380
JAROD, WE DID                   
THE BEST WE COULD.              


316
00:23:36,449 --> 00:23:39,350
            BY MY CALCULATIONS, 
            IT TAKES AT LEAST   
            25 MINUTES...       


317
00:23:39,419 --> 00:23:42,420
            TO GET FROM         
            THE ATHLETIC CENTER 
            TO QUEEN OF MERCY.  


318
00:23:42,488 --> 00:23:44,855
            WHAT EXACTLY        
            DID YOU DO FOR HIM? 


319
00:23:44,924 --> 00:23:47,123
            WATCH HIM FALL      
            DEEPER INTO A COMA? 


320
00:23:47,192 --> 00:23:49,626
RENNERT MADE                    
THE JUDGMENT CALL.              


321
00:23:49,695 --> 00:23:54,464
    I LOOKED AT RENNERT'S RECORD
    FOR THE LAST FIVE YEARS.    


322
00:23:54,533 --> 00:23:58,869
HE TOOK AT LEAST 30 PATIENTS    
TO QUEEN OF MERCY HOSPITAL...   


323
00:23:58,938 --> 00:24:01,071
        THAT SHOULD HAVE GONE   
        SOMEWHERE ELSE.         


324
00:24:01,140 --> 00:24:04,274
    THIRTY PATIENTS             
    WITH EXPENSIVE INJURIES...  


325
00:24:04,343 --> 00:24:06,410
            THAT HAVE INSURANCE 
            TO PAY FOR IT.      


326
00:24:06,479 --> 00:24:11,582
GOD KNOWS HOW MANY OTHER PEOPLE 
ENDED UP LIKE STEVEN CHAMBERS.  


327
00:24:15,821 --> 00:24:19,023
            <i> A DOCTOR HAS TO</i>    
            <i> HAVE ETHICS, JULIE.</i>


328
00:24:19,091 --> 00:24:21,191
            <i> PEOPLE'S LIVES</i>     
            <i> ARE IN THEIR HANDS.</i>


329
00:24:29,135 --> 00:24:34,404
THERE HAD BEEN A-- A HAWKS GAME 
THAT NIGHT, AND WE HIT          
THE SPILLOVER TRAFFIC.          


330
00:24:34,473 --> 00:24:37,407
    WE JUST SAT THERE.          


331
00:24:37,476 --> 00:24:42,079
ALL I COULD DO WAS TO           
TALK TO STEVEN, YOU KNOW,       
TRY TO KEEP HIM AWAKE,          


332
00:24:42,148 --> 00:24:45,115
WHILE RENNERT KEPT TELLING ME,  
"WE'RE DOING THE RIGHT THING."  


333
00:24:45,184 --> 00:24:47,517
        YOU COULD HAVE FILED    
        A COMPLAINT AGAINST HIM.


334
00:24:47,586 --> 00:24:49,853
<i>IT WAS MY FIRST WEEK</i>            
<i>UNDER THE REDS, JAROD.</i>          


335
00:24:49,922 --> 00:24:54,157
IT TOOK ALL THE GUTS I HAD      
JUST TO TELL HIM                
WE WERE GOING THE WRONG WAY.    


336
00:24:55,661 --> 00:24:59,930
RENNERT, HE WARNED ME           
NEVER TO SECOND-GUESS HIM       
IN HIS RIG.                     


337
00:25:02,835 --> 00:25:04,768
<i>I DIDN'T WANT ANY TROUBLE.</i>      


338
00:25:04,837 --> 00:25:10,240
    I JUST-- I JUST             
    WANNA HELP PEOPLE.          


339
00:25:17,850 --> 00:25:21,819
<i>[ Raines ]</i>                      
<i>BROOTS.</i>                         


340
00:25:21,887 --> 00:25:24,288
                MR. RAINES.     


341
00:25:24,357 --> 00:25:26,656
WHERE ARE THEY?                 


342
00:25:30,629 --> 00:25:32,562
                    WHO?        


343
00:25:33,999 --> 00:25:36,166
                I-I'M NOT SURE. 


344
00:25:36,235 --> 00:25:41,605
    UM, THAT IS, I-I KNOW       
    WHERE I THINK THEY MIGHT BE.


345
00:25:41,674 --> 00:25:45,042
        - TELL ME.              
        - WELL, UH--            


346
00:25:45,110 --> 00:25:50,013
    THEY WEREN'T VERY SPECIFIC. 
    THEY BOTH JUST TOOK OFF     
    WITHOUT SAYING MUCH.        


347
00:25:51,417 --> 00:25:54,651
HOW'S YOUR LITTLE GIRL?         


348
00:25:54,720 --> 00:25:56,821
                YOU KNOW, UH,   


349
00:25:56,889 --> 00:26:00,925
THEY-- THEY DID SAY SOMETHING   
ABOUT THE MOUNT PLEASANT HOME.  


350
00:26:00,993 --> 00:26:03,293
            SY-SYDNEY GOES THERE
            FROM TIME TO TIME.  


351
00:26:03,362 --> 00:26:06,463
    I KNOW WHERE HE GOES.       


352
00:26:07,933 --> 00:26:10,267
    [ Nurse ]                   
    I'VE INCREASED THE DOSAGE.  


353
00:26:10,336 --> 00:26:13,870
YOU'RE AWARE                    
IT'S THREE TIMES MORE           
THAN YOU ORIGINALLY REQUESTED?  


354
00:26:13,940 --> 00:26:15,973
            MM-HMM.             
                    ALL RIGHT.  


355
00:26:20,579 --> 00:26:22,512
I HAD NO IDEA.                  


356
00:26:22,581 --> 00:26:25,048
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>NOT MANY PEOPLE DO.</i>             


357
00:26:25,117 --> 00:26:27,851
SYDNEY, WHAT HAPPENED?          


358
00:26:30,623 --> 00:26:32,889
<i>[ Young Jacob ]</i>                 
<i>I'M TALKING ABOUT THE CHILDREN.</i> 


359
00:26:32,958 --> 00:26:35,025
        WHAT'S SO TROUBLING     
        ABOUT CHILDREN,         
        FOR GOD'S SAKES?        


360
00:26:35,094 --> 00:26:38,662
- DO YOU KNOW HOW WE GOT        
  THOSE CHILDREN?               
- I KNOW WHAT I NEED TO KNOW.   


361
00:26:38,730 --> 00:26:40,830
    NO, NO, YOU KNOW            
    WHAT THE CENTRE             
    WANTS YOU TO KNOW.          


362
00:26:40,899 --> 00:26:43,299
<i>YOU-- YOU ALWAYS DO THIS.</i>       


363
00:26:43,368 --> 00:26:46,403
YOU ALWAYS PUSH AWAY            
WHAT DOESN'T FIT INTO YOUR      
PRISTINE VIEW OF THE WORLD.     


364
00:26:46,472 --> 00:26:49,239
    AND ALL YOU WANNA DO        
    IS POISON THE GOOD THINGS   
    IN YOUR LIFE.               


365
00:26:49,308 --> 00:26:52,375
        -<i> SYDNEY!</i>               
        - [ Crash ]             


366
00:26:54,579 --> 00:26:57,014
<i>[ Raining ]</i>                     


367
00:27:08,661 --> 00:27:10,827
            JACOB. JACOB!       


368
00:27:12,265 --> 00:27:14,198
JACOB!                          


369
00:27:24,510 --> 00:27:26,743
            JACOB!              
<i>[ Sydney ]</i>                      
<i>IT WAS MY FAULT.</i>                


370
00:27:26,812 --> 00:27:29,213
<i>I KNEW THE ROAD,</i>                
<i>KNEW EVERY CURVE.</i>               


371
00:27:30,349 --> 00:27:32,516
SYDNEY, IT COULD HAVE           
HAPPENED TO ANYBODY.            


372
00:27:34,420 --> 00:27:37,187
                UH-UH.          


373
00:27:37,256 --> 00:27:41,458
    A LATER SIMULATION BY JAROD 
    SUGGESTED OTHERWISE.        


374
00:27:41,527 --> 00:27:44,194
            I SHOULD BE THE ONE 
            LYING IN THAT BED.  


375
00:27:44,262 --> 00:27:48,532
[ Monitor Beeping ]             


376
00:27:48,600 --> 00:27:51,802
<i>[ Monitor Beeping Faster ]</i>      


377
00:27:55,607 --> 00:27:58,775
    JACOB.                      
     JACOB, ARE YOU THERE?      


378
00:28:02,348 --> 00:28:04,714
            JACOB.              


379
00:28:11,790 --> 00:28:14,658
        "'I SHOULD NOT LET YOU  
          DEPART FROM ME THUS.' 


380
00:28:14,726 --> 00:28:18,829
    "'YOU SHOULD, LADY,         
      AND I KNOW YOU WILL,'     
      REJOINED THE GIRL, RISING.


381
00:28:18,898 --> 00:28:23,266
    'YOU WILL NOT STOP MY GOING 
     BECAUSE I HAVE TRUSTED     
     IN YOUR GOODNESS.'"        


382
00:28:25,538 --> 00:28:28,772
        <i> IT'S A LOVELY STORY.</i>   
        <i> I'M EAGER TO SEE</i>       
        <i> HOW IT TURNS OUT.</i>      


383
00:28:28,841 --> 00:28:32,075
FOR THE BEST, I'M SURE.         
I BROUGHT YOU SOME COFFEE.      


384
00:28:37,116 --> 00:28:39,082
                THANK YOU.      


385
00:28:44,990 --> 00:28:46,923
        I DON'T THINK           
        HE'S GOING TO WAKE UP.  


386
00:28:49,428 --> 00:28:51,494
<i>[ Jarod ]</i>                       
<i>DON'T SAY THAT.</i>                 


387
00:28:53,198 --> 00:28:55,799
            I'VE GIVEN UP HOPE. 


388
00:28:55,868 --> 00:28:57,901
        I KNOW RICHARD HAS TOO. 
        HE JUST WON'T ADMIT IT. 


389
00:28:57,969 --> 00:29:01,305
THERE'S STILL SO MUCH           
YOU COULD TRY.                  
THE HOSPITAL THERAPY--          


390
00:29:01,373 --> 00:29:04,841
                IT FAILED.      
                THE TREATMENT'S 
                RUN ITS COURSE. 


391
00:29:04,910 --> 00:29:07,043
DID THEY TRY                    
INCREASING THE DOSAGE?          


392
00:29:07,112 --> 00:29:11,014
        INCREASING,             
        DECREASING, DILUTING.   
        IT'S JUST NOT WORKING.  


393
00:29:11,083 --> 00:29:13,516
THERE'S ANOTHER THERAPY         
I KNOW ABOUT.                   


394
00:29:14,953 --> 00:29:17,154
IT'S CALLED                     
HALSTROM'S TECHNIQUE.           


395
00:29:20,026 --> 00:29:23,460
YOU CAN'T GIVE UP.              
STEVEN'S FOUGHT SO HARD.        


396
00:29:29,601 --> 00:29:33,904
            THERE'S A BOY       
            IN CLEVELAND.       
            HE NEEDS A HEART.   


397
00:29:40,946 --> 00:29:43,213
            WE'RE TRYING TO     
            DECIDE WHAT TO DO.  


398
00:29:47,886 --> 00:29:50,687
    <i> AT THIS POINT,</i>             
    <i> IT WOULD TAKE A MIRACLE.</i>   


399
00:29:52,057 --> 00:29:56,926
        JUST IN CASE,           
        I WANT TO FINISH THIS   
        WITH HIM, SO...         


400
00:29:56,995 --> 00:29:58,928
        HE KNOWS HOW IT ENDS.   


401
00:30:13,645 --> 00:30:17,714
    <i> "'OF WHAT USE THEN</i>         
     <i> IS THE COMMUNICATION</i>      
     <i> YOU HAVE MADE,' SAID ROSE.</i>


402
00:30:17,783 --> 00:30:19,883
        'THIS MYSTERY           
         MUST BE INVESTIGATED.'"


403
00:30:40,338 --> 00:30:42,405
                    JACOB.      


404
00:30:44,309 --> 00:30:46,710
                [ Sighs ]       


405
00:30:46,779 --> 00:30:49,313
    - I CAN SAVE HIM!           
    - YOU HAVE TO ABORT.        


406
00:30:49,381 --> 00:30:52,483
        I CAN SAVE HIM, SYDNEY. 
        NO!                     


407
00:30:52,551 --> 00:30:56,086
    - YOU CAN'T SAVE            
      EVERYONE, JAROD.          
    - WELL, I HAD TO TRY.       


408
00:30:58,157 --> 00:31:00,924
    - [ Sighs ]                 
    -<i> [ Cell Phone Ringing ]</i>    


409
00:31:03,529 --> 00:31:06,463
            - YES.              
            - SYDNEY.           


410
00:31:06,532 --> 00:31:09,799
        HALSTROM'S TECHNIQUE,   


411
00:31:09,868 --> 00:31:12,503
                IT'S FLAWED.    


412
00:31:12,571 --> 00:31:14,504
            THE EFFECT          
            IS ONLY TEMPORARY.  


413
00:31:15,808 --> 00:31:18,275
THANKS, JAROD. THANKS.          


414
00:31:20,479 --> 00:31:24,782
I HAVE, UH, TRIED TO            
COME HERE AS OFTEN AS I CAN,    


415
00:31:24,850 --> 00:31:27,951
BUT MY WORK                     
KEEPS ME OCCUPIED.              


416
00:31:28,020 --> 00:31:30,420
    I MISS YOU.                 


417
00:31:34,527 --> 00:31:36,760
WERE YOU AWARE                  
ALL THIS TIME?                  


418
00:31:40,199 --> 00:31:44,802
<i>JACOB, THE NIGHT</i>                
<i>OF THE ACCIDENT,</i>                


419
00:31:44,871 --> 00:31:46,803
IT STAYED WITH ME.              


420
00:31:46,872 --> 00:31:51,641
<i>I PROMISED YOU I WOULD DO</i>       
<i>EVERYTHING IN MY POWER</i>          
<i>TO BRING YOU BACK.</i>              


421
00:31:51,710 --> 00:31:54,311
YOU SHOULDN'T BE LYING HERE.    


422
00:31:56,315 --> 00:31:58,482
YOU DIDN'T DESERVE THIS.        


423
00:32:32,418 --> 00:32:36,387
        SL-27?                  


424
00:32:41,126 --> 00:32:45,929
    - WHY WASN'T I TOLD?        
    - IT DOESN'T CONCERN YOU.   


425
00:32:45,998 --> 00:32:48,365
        IT'S CENTRE BUSINESS.   


426
00:32:48,433 --> 00:32:51,836
IS HE AWAKE?                    
        I'D LIKE MY QUESTION    
        ANSWERED.               


427
00:32:51,904 --> 00:32:55,238
    - ANSWER MY QUESTION.       
    - HE'S AWAKE.               


428
00:32:55,308 --> 00:32:58,742
                IS HE TALKING?  
            NOT YET.            


429
00:32:58,811 --> 00:33:02,412
                DON'T LET HIM.  
                    SIR?        


430
00:33:02,481 --> 00:33:05,615
JACOB IS A THREAT               
TO CENTRE INTERESTS.            


431
00:33:05,684 --> 00:33:09,953
    YOU HAVE AN OBLIGATION      
    TO PROTECT THOSE INTERESTS. 


432
00:33:10,022 --> 00:33:12,923
DO YOU HAVE A PROBLEM           
WITH THAT?                      


433
00:33:13,993 --> 00:33:16,026
        NO, SIR.                
            A SWEEPER TEAM...   


434
00:33:16,094 --> 00:33:19,362
        WILL BE SENT            
        TO ASSURE YOU DON'T.    


435
00:33:19,431 --> 00:33:23,066
        MAKE SURE JACOB         
        NEVER WAKES UP AGAIN.   


436
00:33:23,135 --> 00:33:25,469
<i>[ Rolling Thunder ]</i>             


437
00:33:26,772 --> 00:33:28,705
<i>[ Phone Beeps ]</i>                 


438
00:33:33,044 --> 00:33:36,546
HEY. ANOTHER DAY                
ON THE LIFELINE, EH, JAROD?     


439
00:33:36,615 --> 00:33:38,248
                    HMM.        


440
00:33:38,317 --> 00:33:42,185
        MR. RENNERT,            
        WOULD YOU LEAVE         
        MR. RANDOLPH AND ME...  


441
00:33:42,254 --> 00:33:45,922
    - ALONE FOR A MOMENT?       
    - WE WERE JUST ABOUT        
      TO START OUR SHIFT.       


442
00:33:45,991 --> 00:33:50,494
YOU AND I ARE GONNA HAVE TO     
COVER A LITTLE GROUND BEFORE I  
LET YOU OUT ON THE STREET AGAIN.


443
00:33:50,562 --> 00:33:52,629
ALL RIGHT.                      


444
00:33:54,500 --> 00:33:59,569
<i>I RAN A BACKGROUND CHECK</i>        
<i>ON YOU, DESPITE YOUR LACK</i>       
<i>OF PAPERWORK,</i>                   


445
00:33:59,638 --> 00:34:02,439
<i>AND SOME INTERESTING DATA</i>       
<i>SPEWED FORTH.</i>                   


446
00:34:02,508 --> 00:34:05,075
<i>BECAUSE THE ONLY</i>                
<i>JAROD RANDOLPH I COULD FIND</i>     
<i>IN THE STATE ARCHIVES...</i>        


447
00:34:05,144 --> 00:34:07,244
    WEIGHS 286 POUNDS,          


448
00:34:07,313 --> 00:34:09,245
<i>AND HE'S BLACK.</i>                 


449
00:34:13,318 --> 00:34:16,286
IT'S TIME YOU PUT               
YOUR CARDS ON THE TABLE, MISTER.


450
00:34:18,157 --> 00:34:21,458
<i>I CAN'T EVEN VERIFY</i>             
<i>THAT YOU'RE TRAINED</i>             
<i>FOR THIS JOB.</i>                   


451
00:34:21,527 --> 00:34:25,095
AND DESPITE THE MOUNTAIN        
OF PHONE CALLS THAT             
I'VE RECEIVED PRAISING YOU,     


452
00:34:25,164 --> 00:34:29,733
I NEED TO KNOW THAT             
THE PEOPLE YOU'RE ASSISTING     
ARE IN THE RIGHT HANDS.         


453
00:34:31,871 --> 00:34:34,637
        WELL, I GUESS MY LUCK   
        JUST RAN OUT.           


454
00:34:36,208 --> 00:34:38,809
GIMME ONE GOOD REASON           
NOT TO CALL THE COPS.           


455
00:35:05,270 --> 00:35:07,904
    [ No Audible Dialogue ]     


456
00:35:15,280 --> 00:35:19,249
    SO, I HEARD THAT, UM,       
    VARGAS RODE YOU PRETTY HARD 
    LAST NIGHT, HUH?            


457
00:35:19,318 --> 00:35:21,685
I THINK THERE'S GONNA BE        
SOME CHANGES IN THIS UNIT.      


458
00:35:21,753 --> 00:35:23,720
<i>[ Woman ]</i>                       
<i>UNIT 45, THIS IS DISPATCH.</i>      


459
00:35:23,789 --> 00:35:27,357
<i>WE HAVE A CYCLIST DOWN</i>          
<i>ON THE CORNER OF</i>                
<i>PEACHTREE AND DUNWOODY.</i>         


460
00:35:28,761 --> 00:35:32,729
            [ Siren Wailing ]   


461
00:35:32,798 --> 00:35:35,999
<i>[ Man On Radio ] NINE-YEAR-OLD</i>  
<i>MALE WITH A BLOCKED AIRWAY,</i>     
<i>UNCONSCIOUS, NOT BREATHING.</i>     


462
00:35:36,067 --> 00:35:39,402
<i>[ Continues Indistinct ]</i>        
<i>[ Woman ] WE COPY.</i>              


463
00:35:41,373 --> 00:35:43,406
                    [ Groaning ]


464
00:35:48,980 --> 00:35:50,914
                    IT'S OKAY.  
            [ Groans ]          


465
00:35:50,982 --> 00:35:54,184
            GONNA TAKE GOOD CARE
            OF YOU. JUST RELAX. 


466
00:35:54,253 --> 00:35:57,454
        <i> PUPILS ARE UNEVEN.</i>     
        <i> WE SHOULD C-SPINE HIM.</i> 


467
00:35:57,523 --> 00:36:01,425
LOOK AT THAT. GUY CAN AFFORD    
A ROLEX, YOU THINK              
HE'D INVEST IN A HELMET.        


468
00:36:01,494 --> 00:36:04,294
    GUESS I'M THE LAB RAT NOW,  
    HUH, DOC?                   


469
00:36:06,598 --> 00:36:08,731
<i>[ Groaning ]</i>                    


470
00:36:15,874 --> 00:36:18,574
        SYDNEY'S IN THE LOUNGE. 
        KEEP AN EYE OUT.        


471
00:36:25,084 --> 00:36:27,418
MR. RAINES INSISTS I WATCH.     


472
00:37:19,871 --> 00:37:23,473
<i>[ Plastic Gloves Crinkling ]</i>    
            WE'RE DONE HERE.    


473
00:38:05,150 --> 00:38:09,552
HE SLIPPED BACK INTO THE COMA.  
 HE WROTE SOMETHING DOWN FIRST. 


474
00:38:10,723 --> 00:38:12,789
I'M HAPPY FOR YOU.              


475
00:38:34,880 --> 00:38:36,813
        SOMEBODY PAGED ME?      


476
00:38:36,882 --> 00:38:38,948
                <i> THAT WAS ME,</i>   
                <i> DR. COREY.</i>     
    OH.                         


477
00:38:39,017 --> 00:38:42,452
                    HERE.       


478
00:38:42,521 --> 00:38:45,555
WHAT IS THIS?                   
                JAROD WANTED YOU
                TO SEE THIS.    


479
00:38:45,623 --> 00:38:48,091
STEVEN CHAMBERS?                


480
00:38:48,160 --> 00:38:51,627
            A CASE CAN BE MADE  
            FOR NEGLIGENCE      
            ON RENNERT'S PART.  


481
00:38:51,696 --> 00:38:54,297
                YOU MAY WANT TO 
                LISTEN TO THIS. 


482
00:38:54,366 --> 00:38:57,834
        [ Siren Wailing         
          On Walkie-Talkie ]    


483
00:38:57,903 --> 00:38:59,836
        [ Rennert ]             
        UH, QUEEN OF MERCY,     
        THIS IS UNIT 45.        


484
00:38:59,905 --> 00:39:04,273
    WE'VE GOT A DOWN CYCLIST,   
    UH, POSSIBLE HEAD INJURY.   


485
00:39:04,342 --> 00:39:07,911
    QUEEN OF MERCY?             
    GRADY MEMORIAL              
    IS A FASTER RUN.            


486
00:39:07,980 --> 00:39:11,013
I'M NOT GOING THROUGH           
THIS AGAIN, ALL RIGHT?          
QUEEN OF MERCY'S MY CALL.       


487
00:39:11,082 --> 00:39:13,483
RENNERT, THIS GUY               
IS FADING ON ME.                


488
00:39:13,552 --> 00:39:16,753
THEN YOU KEEP HIM ALIVE         
TILL WE GET TO QUEEN OF MERCY!  
COME ON!                        


489
00:39:25,897 --> 00:39:28,431
        [ Chattering ]          


490
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:31,635
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>COMING THROUGH, PEOPLE.</i>         


491
00:39:49,120 --> 00:39:51,621
            [ Knocking ]        


492
00:39:57,062 --> 00:39:58,995
    WHAT ARE YOU DOING HERE?    


493
00:39:59,064 --> 00:40:01,398
    HEY.                        
                    HMM.        


494
00:40:06,972 --> 00:40:09,172
            IS THIS             
            WHAT SOMEONE'S LIFE 
            IS WORTH TO YOU?    


495
00:40:09,241 --> 00:40:11,541
<i>HEY, I DON'T KNOW</i>               
<i>WHAT THIS IS ABOUT.</i>             


496
00:40:11,610 --> 00:40:14,010
    THIS IS ABOUT YOU           
    AND THIS AMBULANCE DRIVER...


497
00:40:14,079 --> 00:40:17,581
    ENDANGERING THE LIVES       
    OF PATIENTS SO YOU CAN      
    CASH IN ON THEIR INSURANCE. 


498
00:40:17,649 --> 00:40:20,884
            <i> IT'S ABOUT WATCHING</i>
            <i> A YOUNG MAN'S LIFE</i> 
            <i> JUST FADE AWAY.</i>    


499
00:40:20,953 --> 00:40:23,219
                STEVEN CHAMBERS 
                TRUSTED YOU.    


500
00:40:23,288 --> 00:40:25,722
                YOU DIDN'T CARE 
                ABOUT HIS LIFE. 


501
00:40:25,791 --> 00:40:28,391
            ALL YOU CARE ABOUT  
            IS WHAT'S INSIDE    
            THIS ENVELOPE.      


502
00:40:28,460 --> 00:40:31,194
NO, NO, NO,                     
THIS IS A SETUP, MAN.           
THIS IS NOT FAIR.               


503
00:40:31,263 --> 00:40:35,232
WHAT'S NOT FAIR IS STEVEN       
CHAMBERS'S PARENTS ARE GONNA    
HAVE TO UNPLUG THE MACHINES...  


504
00:40:35,300 --> 00:40:37,733
        THAT ARE BREATHING LIFE 
        INTO THEIR ONLY SON.    


505
00:40:38,804 --> 00:40:41,404
        - I'M OUTTA HERE.       
        - COME WITH ME, SIR.    


506
00:40:41,473 --> 00:40:44,674
HEY, WAIT A MINUTE.             
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?             
HEY! HEY!                       


507
00:40:44,743 --> 00:40:46,676
OH, MAN.                        


508
00:40:46,745 --> 00:40:50,513
THI--                           
                    OH, RENNERT.


509
00:40:53,786 --> 00:40:56,186
            YOU MIGHT NEED THIS.


510
00:41:08,233 --> 00:41:11,167
"I HAVE SAID THAT               
 THEY WERE TRULY HAPPY;         


511
00:41:11,236 --> 00:41:14,403
"AND WITHOUT STRONG AFFECTION   
  AND HUMANITY OF HEART,        


512
00:41:14,472 --> 00:41:17,640
<i>"AND GRATITUDE TO THAT BEING</i>    
<i> WHOSE CODE IS MERCY,</i>           


513
00:41:23,147 --> 00:41:26,449
AND WHOSE GREAT ATTRIBUTE       
IS BENEVOLENCE TO ALL THINGS    
THAT BREATHE--"                 


514
00:41:26,518 --> 00:41:30,286
WE NEED TO DO THIS.             


515
00:41:30,355 --> 00:41:33,256
<i>"WITHIN THE ALTAR</i>               
<i> OF THE OLD VILLAGE CHURCH...</i>   


516
00:41:33,325 --> 00:41:35,325
        <i> "THERE STANDS</i>          
         <i> A WHITE MARBLE TABLET,</i>


517
00:41:36,728 --> 00:41:39,962
"WHICH BEARS AS YET             
 BUT ONE WORD: 'AGNES.'         


518
00:41:40,031 --> 00:41:42,598
"THERE'S NO COFFIN              
 IN THAT TOMB;                  


519
00:41:42,667 --> 00:41:45,968
<i>"AND MAY IT BE MANY, MANY YEARS</i> 
<i> BEFORE ANOTHER NAME</i>            
<i> IS PLACED ABOVE IT.</i>            


520
00:41:47,406 --> 00:41:50,406
<i>"BUT IF THE SPIRITS OF THE DEAD</i> 
<i> EVER COME BACK TO EARTH...</i>     


521
00:41:50,475 --> 00:41:54,411
<i>"TO VISIT SPOTS HALLOWED</i>        
<i> BY THE LOVE, THE LOVE</i>          
<i> BEYOND THE GRAVE,</i>              


522
00:41:54,479 --> 00:41:57,513
<i>"THOSE WHOM THEY KNEW IN LIFE,</i>  


523
00:41:57,583 --> 00:42:01,217
<i>"I BELIEVE THAT THE SHADE</i>       
<i> OF AGNES SOMETIMES HOVERS</i>      
<i> AROUND THAT SOLEMN NOOK.</i>       


524
00:42:04,022 --> 00:42:06,455
<i>"I BELIEVE IT, NONETHELESS,</i>     


525
00:42:06,524 --> 00:42:09,493
<i>"BECAUSE THAT NOOK</i>              
<i> IS IN A CHURCH...</i>              


526
00:42:09,561 --> 00:42:12,362
<i>"AND SHE WAS WEAK</i>               
<i>  AND ERRING."</i>                  


527
00:42:13,432 --> 00:42:16,833
        [ Sustained Tone ]      


528
00:42:18,136 --> 00:42:20,504
        "THE END."              


529
00:42:23,208 --> 00:42:25,541
        ALL DONE.               


530
00:42:28,947 --> 00:42:31,147
IT'S GOOD THAT OLIVER           
FOUND A FAMILY.                 


531
00:42:33,551 --> 00:42:36,153
        - DARLING.              
        - I KNOW.               


532
00:42:38,257 --> 00:42:40,990
[ Priest Praying,               
  Indistinct ]                  


533
00:42:50,535 --> 00:42:52,802
        [ Sobbing ]             


534
00:43:06,885 --> 00:43:09,152
            GODSPEED, MY SON.   


535
00:43:25,370 --> 00:43:27,537
                [ Sobbing ]     


536
00:43:57,635 --> 00:44:01,437
[ Takes Deep Breath, Exhales ]  


537
00:44:01,506 --> 00:44:03,706
YOU WERE RIGHT, SYDNEY.         


538
00:44:20,559 --> 00:44:24,494
            WELL, I HAVE TO     
            GET BACK TO WORK.   


539
00:44:24,563 --> 00:44:28,298
SO, YOU'RE STAYING.             


540
00:44:28,367 --> 00:44:31,734
        WHO WANTS TO BE AROUND  
        A BUNCH OF MICE ANYWAY? 


541
00:44:37,075 --> 00:44:42,278
                WHERE YOU GOING?
    CLEVELAND.                  


542
00:44:42,347 --> 00:44:45,248
<i>[ Female Dispatcher ]</i>           
<i>AIRLIFT FOUR,</i>                   
<i>WHAT'S YOUR E.T.A.?</i>             


543
00:44:45,317 --> 00:44:48,484
<i>[ Man ]</i>                         
<i>UH, WE'LL BE TOUCHING DOWN</i>      
<i>IN 15 SECONDS. OUT.</i>             


544
00:44:58,196 --> 00:45:00,730
    [ No Audible Dialogue ]     


545
00:45:03,602 --> 00:45:05,969
<i>[ Monitor Beeping ]</i>             


546
00:45:12,210 --> 00:45:14,477
                ANY CHANGE?     
                    NO.         


547
00:45:14,545 --> 00:45:17,914
SINCE HE, UH, SLIPPED BACK      
INTO THE COMA,                  


548
00:45:17,982 --> 00:45:20,816
THERE'S BEEN NOTHING.           


549
00:45:20,885 --> 00:45:24,120
            IT'S NOT FAIR.      
WHAT ISN'T FAIR?                


550
00:45:24,189 --> 00:45:27,823
    SOME PEOPLE,                
    THEY JUST FIGHT SO HARD,    
    BUT THEY JUST DON'T MAKE IT.


551
00:45:27,892 --> 00:45:32,395
    OH, YOU CAN'T SAVE          
    THEM ALL, JAROD.            


552
00:45:32,463 --> 00:45:35,131
YOU MAY BE A PRETENDER,         
BUT YOU'RE HUMAN.               


553
00:45:35,200 --> 00:45:37,667
            RIGHT.              


554
00:45:37,736 --> 00:45:40,536
        HALSTROM'S TECHNIQUE,   


555
00:45:40,605 --> 00:45:42,539
        DID IT HELP AT ALL?     


556
00:45:51,049 --> 00:45:52,982
    IT HELPED ENOUGH.           


557
00:46:00,124 --> 00:46:03,192
        [ Phone Beeps ]         


558
00:46:44,502 --> 00:46:45,535
            [ Mews ]            


